<!-- +++++++++++ Shield +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Shield"><p>
A <b>Shield</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> included 
for suppression of unwanted electromagnetic coupling among components.
An  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> included in the assembly for other purposes might also serve as a <b>Shield</b>, and in that case the other type would be specified as well for that instance.

</p><example number="1">
A <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Via"/> may be a <b>Shield</b>. More than one shield may shield the same <b>shielded_item</b> for the same purpose.
</example>
<example number="2">
<module_ref linkend="Shield_arm:4_entities:figure:shield">Figure 1</module_ref> illustrates a detail of a layout drawing that shows a shielded trace (carrying a critical signal) on the several layers it traverses in the design.
</example>
<figure id="shield">
   <title>Shield</title>
   <img src="shield.gif"/>
</figure>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Shield.shielded_item">
specifies either an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/> as the shieldable item for a <b>Shield</b>.
There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>,  <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>, or  <express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/> for a <b>Shield</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Component_group_external_reference +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Component_group_external_reference">
A <b>Component_group_external_reference</b> is an identifier and information for a group of components used in the shield.

</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Component_group_external_reference.name">
the words by which the <b>Component_group_external_reference</b> is known.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Component_group_external_reference.associated_definition">
specifies a string for the <b>Component_group_external_reference</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Component_group_external_reference.ur:UR1">
<p>
<b>name</b> and <b>associated_definition</b> should be unique within a population of <b>Component_group_external_reference</b>.
</p>
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Integral_shield +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Integral_shield">
An <b>Integral_shield</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Laminate_component"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Integral_shield.shielded_item">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Shield:arm:Shield_arm.laminate_shieldable_item"/> for the <b>Integral_shield</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Physical_shield +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Physical_shield">
An <b>Physical_shield</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Physical_component"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Physical_shield.shielded_item">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Shield:arm:Shield_arm.physical_shieldable_item"/> for the <b>Physical_shield</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Routed_shield +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Routed_shield">
A <b>Routed_shield</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_with_printed_component_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_with_printed_component_design_arm.Routed_printed_component"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Routed_shield.shielded_item">
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Shield:arm:Shield_arm.physical_shieldable_item"/> for the <b>Routed_shield</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Physical_connectivity_definition_external_reference +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition_external_reference">
A <b>Physical_connectivity_definition_external_reference</b> is an identifier and information for the physical connectivity used in the shield.

</ext_description>
